comments: Bridges (CHA) and Westbrook (WAS) come together at the same spot and incidental body contact occurs as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Beal (WAS) establishes himself in the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Bridges (CHA) has his forearm slightly extended forward when marginal contact occurs with Westbrook's (WAS) front at the end of the drive.
Graham (CHA) moves alongside Smith's (WAS) path and maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) has his hand rested on Rozier's (CHA) front and marginal contact occurs during Rozier's driving shot attempt.
Zeller (CHA) engages and disengages with Lopez (WAS) as he moves to set the pick.
Graham (CHA) legally contests Smith's (WAS) jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Smith's right foot as he returns to the floor.
Zeller (CHA) slightly extends his right side outward as he sets the pick on Westbrook (WAS) and absorbs the contact.
Zeller (CHA) is deemed to be in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Hachimura (WAS) legally contests Ball's (CHA) jump shot attempt. Any arm contact that occurs after the release is deemed incidental.
Lopez (WAS) engages and disengages with Zeller (CHA) as marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Biyombo (CHA) engages and disengages with Lopez (WAS) along the perimeter.
Rozier (CHA) and Westbrook (WAS) come together during the drive and Rozier absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs.
Bridges (CHA) turns away from Westbrook (WAS) and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs at the end of the drive.
Biyombo (CHA) makes contact to Lopez's (WAS) body and face that affects his ability to get to the rebound.
Zeller (CHA) establishes himself in a screening position in Hachimura's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Ball (CHA) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
Westbrook (WAS) commits a take foul on Rozier (CHA).
